      "text": "\nI've found in programming that having all code in a revision control system gives great encouragement to the act of deleting stuff that is no longer needed.  After all, you say, \"if someone finds out tomorrow that they need it, it can be recovered from RCS.\"  Most of the time you never go back and look at the deleted stuff ever again, but it sure makes you feel better to know that you can.  -- [[Jeff Grigg]] [<i>Ditto. -- [[Tim Chambers]]</i>]",
